-- Cotton Futures in New York Drop 0.2%, Decline for First Time in Five Days
-- B y   J a e   H u r
-- 2010-11-04T01:21:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/cotton-futures-in-new-york-drop-0-2-decline-for-first-time-in-five-days.html
Cotton futures declined, snapping a
four-day winning streak on ICE Futures U.S. in New York.  The contract for December delivery dropped as much as 0.4
percent, erasing an early 1.2 percent jump, and traded 0.2
percent lower at $1.352 a pound at 9:20 a.m. in Singapore.  To contact the reporter on this story:
